China is constructing its first blood bank for pandas to aid in research on their blood types and transfusion compatibility.
With only 1,600 pandas in the wild, efforts are crucial to protect the species.
The Qinling pandas, separated from the giant panda 50,000 years ago, are particularly vulnerable.
Threats like poaching and habitat loss persist, with bamboo shortages causing deaths.
Conservation measures include establishing reserves and planting bamboo.
Recent snowfall in Sichuan has endangered pandas, highlighting the ongoing challenges faced by these iconic animals.
Efforts continue to safeguard their future through habitat protection and rescue operations.
